<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="020" project="spaarke-matter-ui-enhancement-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>DonutChart fieldPivot consumption + matrixRight layout + colorThresholds segments (FR-VH-01)</title>
    <phase>2: Visual Host Renderer Extensions</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5-7</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>002</dependencies>
    <blocks>025</blocks>
    <tags>pcf, react, fluent-ui, frontend, visualhost</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Code in PCF renderer touching production-shipping Visual Host with ADR-021 (Fluent v9 tokens) + ADR-022 (React 16/17) + NFR-05 binding backward-compat constraints</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend the existing `DonutChart` renderer in Visual Host with generic Custom Options keys per FR-VH-01: `donutLayout` ("standard"|"matrixRight", default "standard"), `donutCenterMode` ("total"|"meanOfFields"), `donutCenterLabel`, `showBreakdownRows`, `breakdownValueFormat`. Enable field-pivot consumption in `ChartRenderer.tsx` for the Donut case (today it only supports aggregation). Implement the `matrixRight` layout: donut on the left + breakdown rows on the right in a grid. When `donutCenterMode: "meanOfFields"`, compute `mean(fieldPivot.fields[].value)` and render in the donut center (use `valueFormat: "letterGrade"` thresholds if applicable). Segment colors derive from `colorThresholds[].tokenSet` via the existing `getTokenSetColors()` helper in `MetricCardMatrix.tsx` (line 138). BACKWARD COMPAT (NFR-05): chart defs without `donutLayout` (or with `"standard"`) and no `fieldPivot` MUST render exactly as today.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React + Fluent UI v9 developer with deep familiarity with the Visual Host renderer architecture (ChartRenderer, FieldPivotService, cardConfigResolver 3-tier merge) and the Spaarke chart-definition contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `DonutChart.tsx` and `ChartRenderer.tsx` updated to support the five new generic Custom Options keys. `ChartRenderer.tsx` Donut case now consumes `fieldPivot` data path (in addition to aggregation). `matrixRight` layout renders donut + labeled breakdown rows grid using Fluent v9 tokens only. All existing in-production Donut chart defs render byte-identically to before. Builds clean with `npm run build:prod`. Code-review + adr-check pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-VH-01 is the most NFR-05-sensitive renderer change. It enables the Matter Health Composite chart (FR-DV-01) which needs a donut surrounded by 3 labeled rows for area compliance scores + a composite letter grade in the center derived from `meanOfFields`. Per design.md §6.4.0 binding constraint, this MUST be done by extending the existing `DonutChart` (no new visual types, no Matter-specific code paths). Segment colors must reuse `getTokenSetColors()` from `MetricCardMatrix.tsx:138` so all renderers share one token-set vocabulary.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/DonutChart.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/ChartRenderer.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/MetricCardMatrix.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/services/FieldPivotService.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/configurations/cardConfigResolver.ts</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-VH-01 — generic addition to DonutChart only; no new visual types</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">§6.4.0 (binding) — NO Matter-specific code paths inside Visual Host components</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-05 (binding) — every existing chart def must render unchanged; task 025 will verify</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-VH-01 — backward compat: `donutLayout` absent or `"standard"` + no `fieldPivot` ⇒ identical to today</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 semantic tokens only — zero hex/rgb literals in touched files</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 16/17 platform — no React 18+ APIs (no `useId`, no `useSyncExternalStore`, no concurrent features)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">No new Fluent v8 imports (`@fluentui/react`) — v9 only (`@fluentui/react-components`)</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-pcf-platform-libraries.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-portal-gotcha.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-theming.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/pcf/control-initialization.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/pcf/modern-theming.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/PCF-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/VISUALHOST-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-matter-ui-enhancement-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Token-set color helper" location="src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/MetricCardMatrix.tsx (line 138)">
        `getTokenSetColors(tokenSet)` returns { fill, foreground } pairs per token set (brand / success / warning / danger / neutral). REUSE — do not duplicate.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Field-pivot service" location="src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/services/FieldPivotService.ts">
        Resolves `fieldPivot.fields[].field` against the record producing `{label, value, badge?}` rows. Already wired for MetricCard / MetricCardMatrix — extend Donut to consume the same shape.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Custom Options merge" location="src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/configurations/cardConfigResolver.ts">
        Three-tier merge (chart-def → defaults → runtime). New keys are added to the resolved options shape; provide sensible defaults so backward-compat path stays identical.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Step 0.5: Invoke `Skill fluent-v9-component` — binding per design.md §6.0 for every UI task. Load Fluent v9 patterns (portal gotcha, theming, React version boundaries).</step>
    <step order="1">Read DonutChart.tsx, ChartRenderer.tsx, MetricCardMatrix.tsx (getTokenSetColors), FieldPivotService.ts, cardConfigResolver.ts to anchor the existing contract and identify the NFR-05 baseline behavior.</step>
    <step order="2">Update the Donut options type in cardConfigResolver.ts (or shared types module) to add: `donutLayout?: "standard" | "matrixRight"`, `donutCenterMode?: "total" | "meanOfFields"`, `donutCenterLabel?: string`, `showBreakdownRows?: boolean`, `breakdownValueFormat?: "score" | "scoreOver100" | "percentage" | "ratio"`. Defaults: donutLayout = "standard", donutCenterMode = "total".</step>
    <step order="3">In ChartRenderer.tsx Donut case: if `fieldPivot` is present, route through FieldPivotService (mirroring MetricCard's path). If absent, preserve the current aggregation-only path BYTE-IDENTICALLY.</step>
    <step order="4">In DonutChart.tsx: branch on `donutLayout`. "standard" path = unchanged from today. "matrixRight" path = CSS grid (donut column + breakdown rows column) using Fluent v9 `tokens.spacingHorizontal*` for gaps.</step>
    <step order="5">Implement center value: when `donutCenterMode: "meanOfFields"`, compute mean of `fieldPivot.fields[].value`; format via existing `valueFormat` helper (letterGrade producing "B+", scoreOver100 producing "85/100", etc.). Honor `donutCenterLabel` as the small label above the centerpiece.</step>
    <step order="6">Implement breakdown rows when `showBreakdownRows: true`: each row = uppercase small-caps label (Fluent `tokens.fontSizeBase200`, `tokens.colorNeutralForeground2`) + formatted value (`tokens.fontSizeBase400`, `tokens.colorNeutralForeground1`). Use `breakdownValueFormat` for row value formatting.</step>
    <step order="7">Segment colors: import or re-export `getTokenSetColors` from MetricCardMatrix.tsx (extract to a shared util if cleaner — but DO NOT duplicate the map). Map each `colorThresholds[]` entry to its segment color via `tokenSet`.</step>
    <step order="8">Backward-compat verification: locally re-render every Donut chart def listed in `notes/spikes/visualhost-chart-def-inventory.md` (output of task 001). Capture screenshots in `notes/spikes/visualhost-regression-evidence/donut-baseline/`. Pixel-diff must be ZERO for chart defs without the new keys.</step>
    <step order="9">Build verification: `npm run build:prod` in VisualHost. Zero TypeScript errors. Bundle size delta noted.</step>
    <step order="9.5">FULL rigor quality gates: invoke `Skill code-review` then `Skill adr-check` — block until both pass. ADR-021 token check, ADR-022 React version check, NFR-05 backward-compat evidence.</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 020 → ✅. Update current-task.md to next pending task.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build PCF (`npm run build:prod`)</tool>
    <tool name="pcf-deploy">Deploy VisualHost PCF to dev for regression smoke (task 025 runs full smoke)</tool>
    <tool name="git">Version control</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/DonutChart.tsx</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/ChartRenderer.tsx</output>
